    "attributes": {
        "action": "Conduct an inquiry into the Ombudsman Scheme for Financial Services (FOS)",
        "additional_details": "The Ombudsman operating under the Financial Services & Markets Act 2000 scheme is meant to provide complainants with an independent means of redress. We do not feel the current Ombudsman achieves this.\r\n\r\nThe inquiry must look into how cases reported to the Ombudsman Independent Assessor are handled, its effectiveness at protecting the public & whether the existing scheme adequately protects the public. This should include reviewing all complaints not upheld/dismissed over the last 10 years.",
        "background": "Commission an inquiry into the Ombudsman scheme that operates under the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000.\r\n\r\nWe believe the current Ombudsman scheme for financial services is not fit for purpose & fails to take appropriate action in respect of many cases that are reported to them.",
